![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/d015b99e-cfbd-411e-afc9-4253a8d939a7/e307.jpg?format=original)

The Boys upped the ante when it comes to commentary on the overall superhero genre, using gore, foul language and sex to do so. It's spin-off, Gen V hopes to shock audiences in a similar fashion, but does it get the job done? Join us as we discuss the latest entry in The Boys universe, which in and of itself tackles a lot of young adult issues complete with the added drama of superpowers. Does it stick the (superhero) landing? Check out our review to find out!  
  
Please leave us a **_review_** on [**ITunes**](https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/major-issues-podcast/id1321720972) so we can grow our audience and grow as podcasters! Rate us wherever podcasts are found. Don't forget to check out our merchandise! All episodes of Major Issues are brought to you by **ComicBook Clique**, the only stop for the latest and greatest things to come to comic books and comic book media.  

